This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses knowledge distillation and model compression techniques, which are common topics in the sub-categories of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of transformers, which are a type of neural network architecture commonly used in natural language processing, but also in computer vision tasks, suggesting that "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also possible sub-categories.
